args: ▷Looks like this is where\nthe imperials are hiding.◁

Enemy numbers unknown—but mere
soldiers are not our greatest problem.
▷Yeah, I'm more worried about that pile
of magical weapons behind them.◁
▷Guess Luca was right—this squad is in\ncharge of recovering stuff like that.◁
▷They're unconscious, but alive.\nLet's get them out of there.◁
Negative. We cannot permit the\nmagical weapons to be activated.\nCareful planning is in order.
▷Could we use Eden mode to take out\nthe entire stockpile at once?◁
Possibly. Can you sustain Eden mode?
▷If Luca's life is on the line? You bet.\nBesides, if we're just destroying weapons,\nI have no reason to hesitate.◁
▷Okay, we made it in. Let's get rid of\nthose weapons before they're activated.◁\nAffirmative. Mode shift...
The records claim the leader of the\ncombat androids has a heart—which\nmeans it will try to save its friends.
This is an ambush.\n▷Oh, do you think?!◁
New directive. Switching Eden mode\nattack target to imperial forces.
Its eyes went green again! ...No matter.\nCapture that thing, men—even if you\nhave to dent it up a little!
I will not be dented. I will not be taken.
▷Ngh! This is... It's so horrible...◁\nYou must endure it, Mascula.
Eden mode disengaged again?\nHmph. Initiating tactical retreat.
It's running! After it, all of you!
Perimeter security is...lacking.\nBut it will offer temporary refuge.
▷I'm so sorry, Laxi. It seems like\nall I ever do is hold you back.◁
▷I know this is how war is—I'm not naive.\nI know that in my head, but my heart...◁
▷Luca's life is in danger. Those are the\nstakes, and I swore I would do this!◁
▷But I just can't convince myself that\nit's all right to take a person's life.◁
▷I have to. I know that. But still, I...◁
Negative. There is no need for\nyour heart to desire bloodshed.
You will continue to hesitate in battles.\nPeople will die, and you will hurt.
That is your nature, Mascula—and it is\nwhy I feel I can synchronize with you now.
You went against your nature in order\nto fight with me. Now it is my turn.
▷But is that even possible? You've always\nsaid I was incomprehensible to you.◁
Affirmative. In its most literal sense,\nyou are impossible for me to comprehend.\nThat will likely remain the case.
But your kindness changed the hearts\nof those who hated me.
They wished to destroy me, yet they put\ntheir faith in you: a combat android.\nOne even risked his life for us.
I have glimpsed the value of mercy for\none's enemies. And that, I understand.
There it is! Don't let it escape!
There is no more time. Mascula.\nRequesting Eden mode reactivation.
▷Laxi, give me the strength to fight!◁
Granted. Now give me the kindness\nrequired to temper my actions.\n▷Heh. Take all you need!◁
Armored regalia fully locked.\nMana kiln stable.
▷System strain falling. Laxi, are we...?◁\nAffirmative. Synchronization complete.
Gah! It's coming right for us!
All hostiles, surrender at once.\nFailure to do so will result in...
Connecting to Fig. Set output to full power.
Wh-what in blazes was that?!\nIs everyone all right?!
Sir, that thing targeted the weapon\nstockpile! They're all gone!
▷I repeat, surrender at once!◁\nOr Fig's next target will be you.
Lieutenant, it's too strong for us...
Our ideals will never falter—nor will our\nrage at the loss of our brothers and sisters.
But as an officer of the Dyrenell Empire,\nI can't order my people to their slaughter.
We surrender, android. Name your terms.
▷Did you hear that, Laxi?!◁\nAffirmative. Concluding operation.
